flowRoot.flowPara: A villager is a single worker process that is spawned by Cluster to handle the incoming HTTP connections.
The chief is a process that runs on each machine and delegates work to the villagers.
The war chief, while not required in the stack adds the ability to coordinate and monitor each of the villages in the stack.
This document outlines the various flavours of architecture that can be implemented as part of commissioning Sidelab's nodeSTACK.
The single trip architecture is the simplest architecture for a nodeSTACK.
As the load for your application increases, you can easily add additional machines to service that load. In this configuration, however, neither machine is aware of the other.

As the need for high-availability increases, the nodeSTACK can scale quite simply through the incorporation of a "War Chief" box. The War Chief is takes on a role of coordinating operations across the "villages".
